        <body>
            <head>F31 [Gaede]</head>

            <div type="edition" subtype="fragment" xml:id="gaede.item_41" n="a" xml:lang="grc">
                <ab>
                    <seg type="context" resp="t" n="1">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg5026.tlg001:@Ῥῆσος-@ὀγδοήκοντα">Schol. T Il. 12. 20a:</ref> (= Eust. 889, 59) 
                        <geogName type="river" key="rhesus" nymRef="Ῥῆσος Ῥοείτης" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511398">Ῥῆσος</geogName>: 
                        <geogName corresp="rhesus" nymRef="Ῥῆσος Ῥοείτης">Ῥοίστης</geogName> (l. <geogName corresp="rhesus" nymRef="Ῥῆσος Ῥοείτης Ῥοείτης">Ῥοείτης</geogName>) 
                        μετωνόμασται. ῥεῖ δὲ πρὸς ἄρκτον ἀπὸ 
                        <geogName type="mountain" key="kalepeuke" nymRef="Καλὴ πεύκη" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550607">καλῆς πεύκης</geogName> 
                        ἥτις ἀπέχει ἀπὸ Ἀδραμυττείου στάδια <num value="80">ρπ</num>. 
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="cf" resp="strabo" xml:id="gaede.item_42" n="2">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001:13.1.44@πάλιν-13.1.44@ἐστιν">Str. 13.1.44 [602]</ref>
                        Πάλιν δ᾿ οὕτως φησίν (ὁ <persName key="demetriosskepsis" nymRef="Δημήτριος ὁ Σκήψιος"><name>Δημήτριος</name></persName>)
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="fragment" resp="demetios" xml:id="troic-diac" n="3">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001.radt:13.1.44@ὁ[2]-13.1.44@ἐστιν"/>
                        <cit>
                            <quote>ὁ μὲν <geogName type="river" key="rhesus" nymRef="Ῥῆσος Ῥοείτης" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511398">Ῥῆσος</geogName>
                                ποταμὸς νῦν καλεῖται <geogName type="river" corresp="rhesus" nymRef="Ῥῆσος Ῥοείτης">Ῥοείτης</geogName>, 
                                εἰ μὴ ἄρα <geogName cert="unknown" type="river" key="unknown">ὁ εἰς τὸν 
                                    <geogName type="river" key="granicus" nymRef="Γράνικος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511260">Γράνικον</geogName> ἐμβάλλων **</geogName>
                                <geogName type="river" key="rhesus" nymRef="Ῥῆσος Ῥοείτης" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511398">Ῥῆσός</geogName> ἐστιν.</quote>
                        </cit>
                    </seg>
                </ab>
            </div>

            <div type="edition" subtype="fragment" xml:id="gaede.item_43" n="b" xml:lang="grc">
                <ab>
                    <seg type="context" resp="t" n="1">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg5026.tlg001:@Κάρησος-@Αἴσηπον">Schol. T Il. 12. 20c:</ref>
                        <geogName type="river" key="caresus" nymRef="Κάρησος Πίδυς" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511287">Κάρησος</geogName>:
                        <geogName type="river" corresp="caresus" nymRef="Κάρησος Πίδυς">Πίδυς</geogName> καλεῖται. ῥεῖ δὲ ἀπὸ 
                        <geogName type="mountain" key="maloeis" nymRef="Μαλόεις" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550717">Μαλοῦντος</geogName> 
                        (cod. ἁπλοῦντος corr. Hercher). <placeName type="ethnic" key="cyzicus" nymRef="Κύζικος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511218">Κυζικηνοὶ</placeName> 
                        ὀξυτόνως αὐτὸν καλοῦσιν. ἐμβάλλει γὰρ εἰς <geogName type="river" key="aesepus" nymRef="Αἴσηπος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511141">Αἴσηπον</geogName>. 
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="cf" xml:id="gaede.item_44" resp="strabo" n="2">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001:13.1.44@κάρησος-13.1.44@αἴσηπον">Str. 13.1.44 [C603]</ref>
                             <geogName type="river" key="caresus" nymRef="Κάρησος Πίδυς" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511287">Κάρησος</geogName> 
                             δ᾿ ἀπὸ <geogName type="mountain" key="maloeis" nymRef="Μαλόεις" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550717">Μαλοῦντος</geogName> 
                             ῥεῖ, τόπου τινὸς κειμένου μεταξὺ <placeName type="city" key="palaiskepsis" nymRef="Παλαίσκηψις Παλαισκήψις"  ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550800">Παλαισκήψεως</placeName> 
                             καὶ <placeName type="city" key="achaiion" nymRef="Ἀχαίιον" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550398">Ἀχαιίου</placeName> τῆς 
                             <geogName type="ethnic" key="tenedos" nymRef="Τένεδος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550912">Τενεδίων <geogFeat>περαίας</geogFeat></geogName>, 
                             ἐμβάλλει δὲ εἰς τὸν <geogName type="river" key="aesepus" nymRef="Αἴσηπος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511141">Αἴσηπον</geogName>· 
                    </seg>
                    
                </ab>
            </div>

            <div type="edition" subtype="fragment" xml:id="gaede.item_45" n="c" xml:lang="grc">
                <ab>
                    <seg type="context" resp="t" n="1">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg5026.tlg001:@Ῥοδίος-@ξ">Schol. T Il. 12. 20e:</ref>
                        <geogName type="river" key="rhodius" nymRef="Ῥοδίος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/501590">Ῥοδίος</geogName>:
                        <geogName corresp="rhodius" nymRef="Ῥοδίος Δάρδανος">Δάρδανος</geogName> καλεῖται. ῥεῖ δὲ ἀπὸ 
                        <placeName corresp="kleandria" nymRef="Κλεανδρία Κλεωνδρία">Κλεωνδρίας</placeName> 
                        (l. <placeName type="city" key="kleandria" nymRef="Κλεανδρία" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/554258">Κλεανδρίας</placeName>) 
                        ἐχούσης (l. ἀπεχούσης) <geogName type="mountain" key="kalepeuke" nymRef="Καλὴ πεύκη" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550607">Πεύκης</geogName> 
                        (l. καλής πεύκης) σταδίους <num value="60">ξ</num>. 
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="cf" resp="hesych" xml:id="gaede.item_46" xml:lang="grc" n="2">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4085.tlg002.latte:Ῥοδίος">Hesych. s.v. Ῥοδίος:</ref>
                            <geogName type="river" key="rhodius" nymRef="Ῥοδίος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/501590">Ῥοδίος</geogName>·
                        ποταμός· ὁ νῦν <geogName corresp="rhodius" nymRef="Ῥοδίος Δάρδανος">Δάρδανος</geogName>.
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="cf" xml:id="gaede.item_47" resp="strabo" n="3">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001:13.1.44@ῥοδίος-13.1.44@αἴνιον">Str.13.1.44 [C603]</ref>
                            <geogName type="river" key="rhodius" nymRef="Ῥοδίος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/501590">Ῥοδίος</geogName> δὲ ἀπὸ
                            <placeName type="city" key="kleandria" nymRef="Κλεανδρία" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/554258">Κλεανδρίας</placeName> 
                            καὶ <placeName type="city" key="gordon" nymRef="Γόρδον">Γόρδου</placeName>, ἃ διέχει τῆς 
                            <geogName type="mountain" key="kalepeuke" nymRef="Καλὴ πεύκη" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550607">Καλῆς πεύκης</geogName>
                            ἑξήκοντα σταδίους, ἐμβάλλει δ᾿ εἰς τὸν <geogName type="river" key="ainios" nymRef="Αἴνιος">Αἴνιον</geogName>. 
                    </seg>
                </ab>
            </div>
                    


            <div type="apparatus"/>

            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" n="1">
                <ab>
                <seg type="context" resp="t" n="a">
                    <title>Schol. T Il. 12. 20a:</title> (= Eust. 889, 59) 
                    <geogName type="river" key="rhesus" nymRef="Ῥῆσος Ῥοείτης"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511398">Rhesos</geogName>: it was
                    renamed <geogName corresp="rhesus" nymRef="Ῥοείτης">Rhoeites</geogName>. It
                        flows towards the north, down from the <geogName type="mountain"
                            key="kalepeuke" nymRef="Καλὴ πεύκη"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550607">Beautiful Pine</geogName>,
                        which is 180 stadia away from <placeName type="city" key="adramyttium"
                            nymRef="Ἀδραμύττιον" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550403"
                            >Adramytteion</placeName>.
                </seg>
                

                    <seg type="context" resp="t" n="b"><title>Schol. T Il. 12. 20c:</title> 
                        <geogName type="river" key="caresus" nymRef="Κάρησος Πίδυς"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511287">Karesos</geogName>: it is
                        called <geogName type="river" corresp="caresus" nymRef="Πίδυς"
                            >Pitys</geogName>. It flows down from <geogName type="mountain"
                            key="maloeis" nymRef="Μαλόεις"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550717">Malus</geogName>. The
                            <placeName type="ethnic" key="cyzicus" nymRef="Κύζικος"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511218">inhabitants of
                            Cyzicus</placeName> pronounce it with an acute accent. It flows into the
                            <geogName type="river" key="aesepus" nymRef="Αἴσηπος"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511141">Aesepos</geogName>.
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="context" resp="t" n="c"><title>Schol. T Il. 12. 20e:</title>
                        <geogName type="river" key="rhodius" nymRef="Ῥοδίος"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/501590">Rhodios</geogName>: it is
                        called <geogName corresp="rhodius" nymRef="Δάρδανος">Dardanos</geogName>. It
                        flows down from <placeName type="city" key="kleandria" nymRef="Κλεανδρία"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/554258">Kleandria</placeName>,
                        which is sixty stadia away from the <geogName type="mountain"
                            key="kalepeuke" nymRef="Καλὴ πεύκη"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550607"> Beautiful
                        Pine</geogName>.
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="cf" resp="hesych" n="1"> <title>Hesych. s.v. Ῥοδίος:</title> 
                        <geogName type="river" key="rhodius" nymRef="Ῥοδίος"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/501590">Rhodios</geogName>: a
                        river. The present <geogName corresp="rhodius" nymRef="Δάρδανος"
                            >Dardanos</geogName>.
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="cf" resp="strabo" n="2">
                        The
                        <geogName type="river" key="rhodius" nymRef="Ῥοδίος"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/501590">Rhodios</geogName> flows
                        down from <placeName type="city" key="kleandria" nymRef="Κλεανδρία"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/554258">Kleandria</placeName> and
                        <placeName type="city" key="gordon" nymRef="Γόρδον">Gordos</placeName>,
                        which are at 60 stadia away from the <geogName type="mountain"
                            key="kalepeuke" nymRef="Καλὴ πεύκη"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550607">Beautiful Pine</geogName> ,
                        and empties into the <geogName type="river" key="ainios" nymRef="Αἴνιος"
                            >Ainion</geogName>.
                    </seg>
                </ab>
            </div>
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <p/>
            </div>

